pageTitle: Cardiff City - Plymouth Star Expects Cardiff 'Test'
TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {10529=Trollope Accepts Welsh Position (Wednesday July 22 2015), 21299=Plymouth Argyle's experienced striker Barry Hayles is looking forward to an intense run of games for the Pilgrims but is first concentrating on this weekend's showdown with Cardiff City, a match he sees as a 'test' for his side. Speaking on his icons.com homepage, Hayles highlighted the new additions to Cardiff's squad: 'Cardiff are our visitors this Saturday and they are going to put us to the test. They have brought in some quality players, especially the boys up front Robbie Fowler and Jimmy Flyd Hasselbaink. They are big name players who have been there and done that.' Hayles expects his side to do well however, and pointed to thie attacking line-up as a source of strength for the home side. 'I think we're looking very strong now and up front we have four strikers who are all scoring.' Plymouth are a decent side, and Cardiff are still yet to gel as a new squad.
